description:
For sale: $254,900. There is so much you're going to love about living here! This ideal end unit with an open floor plan has phenomenal city-views. description: For sale: $434,900. Welcome to the luxurious Portland Tower! This wonderful corner unit has the ideal open floorplan featuring walls of windows that pour in natural light and feature gorgeous Minneapolis views! Tons of fabulous restaurants, parks, and farmers market even USBank Stadium are just blocks away! Enjoy in-building exclusive amenities such as an exercise facility, common room with a full kitchen, pet area, and more! This unit comes with 2 parking spots plus additional storage space in the heated and secure garage. The kitchen highlights stunning granite countertops, custom cherry cabinets, and an oversized island with built-in wine fridge! The adjacent living area is brightly lit with wall-length windows that come with custom shades, beautifully complementing the brilliant hardwood floors! The owner's suite boasts views of the Clock Tower at City Hall and has remote-controlled, darkening shades! You'll love the well-planned master setup with a lavish bath and huge closet! See it today!
Zestimate® Home Value: $256,154. This 755 square foot condo home has 1 bedrooms and 1.0 bathrooms. It is located at 401 S 1st St Minneapolis, Minnesota.

description: For sale: $310,000. Modern condo with stainless steel appliances, black granite countertops, cherry cabinets, laminate flooring, Kohler faucets, washer and dryer. Great river view with balcony; offers prime viewing for fireworks displays over the Mississippi river!  Fantastic location within walking distance to the Stone Arch Bridge, the Guthrie Theater, the Organic Farmer's Market, the Minneapolis Depot, and the historic St. Anthony Main district and all of downtown! Easy access to miles of biking and walking trails. 2 blocks to access Skyway.  Clean, friendly building with numerous amenities including outdoor pool and sundeck, party and media room for entertaining guests, fitness center, sauna and hot tub.

For sale: $689,900. Penthouse plus highly sought-after views! Great full wall of south & east windows plus patio views of the downtown skyline. Nighttime lights are not to be missed! Hardwood floors finished on-site, custom cabinetry with honed quartz island and quartz perimeter. High-end monogram appliances, plus washer & dryer included. Very open & spacious living area plus two bedrooms. 2 parking stalls included - association has approved electric outlets for cars. Enhanced tile choices, lighting & plumbing fixtures - so all the extras are already included! Portland Tower offers many amenities including a fitness center and community room with a kitchen designed for entertaining. Finished model in Portland Tower - other models available for quick closings.  AT THIS TIME, SHOWINGS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please complete attached document before viewing.

Skyway connected so you can walk to work, dining, shopping, sporting events, and so much more from this perfect downtown location. Stainless steel appliances, wide plank woods floors and an updated bathroom makes this turnkey!

This open plan offers stunning Skyline and Mississippi River views, plus enchanting sunsets. Uniquely bright and airy due to its very open concept, 10.5ft ceilings and walls of glass. Modern updates make the spaces even more functional and beautiful. New sustainable Wisconsin Oak floors throughout. Suite 1, looking South over the City, was remodeled w/new built-ins and redone  BA. Suite 2, w/views to the River, has updated dual vanity 3/4 BA and large walk-in closet. 3rd BR or office offers a "work from home perch" squarely looking over the City. Remodeled 3rd BA w/signature soaking tub and dramatic wall tile. Custom family room and bedroom built-ins, updated lighting and automatic shade controllers. Enjoy 2 adjacent parking spots on P6 and a private, large (80sf) storage rm. Building common area updates to be completed by June without assessment (resident flrs, new clubroom and more).

For sale: $499,900. Beautifully maintained 2 bedroom, 2 bath city condo with views in three directions. Enjoy the wonderful outdoors from 2 balconies or additional over sized inviting terrace. description: For sale: $234,000. Built from the ground up in 2007, 730 Lofts is the epitome of contemporary urban living in the North Loop. description: For sale: $1,800,000. This custom, updated 3BR/3BA residence perches you above the Mississippi River w/views to the Stone Arch Bridge and Mill District. This spacious 2,282 sq ft unit has a stunning marble master BA remodel, redone powder BA, new appliances and more. Enjoy the river, grilling and eye-level firework displays from your 2 balconies. This Thoreau floor plan has gracious spaces, including large kitchen w/Sub-Zero French door refrigerator, Bosch Wall Oven and Microwave, Wolf Gas Cooktop and Miele Dishwasher. Master BA has been enhanced w/pocket doors to streamline the suite, which includes double vanity, private commode and walk in closet. Family rm captures the River, St. Anthony Falls and Stone Arch while still warming up with a gas fplc and mounted TV. 3rd BR is being used as an office. Amenities refresh underway, w/no assessment, to be complete early 2020. 1/2 block from the Skyway, The Carlyle (24-hr attendant, fitness, pool, guest suites, great room) offers premiere downtown living in the Mills District!

For sale: $3,195,000. Mill District one-of-a-kind loft penthouse in the historic North Star Lofts, a former woolen blanket mill on the National Registry of Historic Places. This spectacular home overlooks the mighty Mississippi River, St. Anthony Falls, and the Stone Arch Bridge. A private 26' x 22' rooftop deck with panoramic views is accessible directly from the unit. Custom, updated finishes throughout. Expansive open floor plan with soaring ceilings, oversized windows, light-filled living spaces, custom fireplace surround, and exposed limestone brick walls adding character and a sense of place against the dramatic riverfront views. A 3400 square foot corner plan that lives like a private townhome with three attached parking spaces and a secondary entrance. 3 bedrooms on one level, luxurious master suite with corner views, mezzanine-level den, upper level studio/office. 3 BR, 3 BA, 3 garage stalls. Storage. This is a must see and the first time it has been available on the open market.

description: Recently sold: $325,000. Location, Location, Location! Welcome to Tower Lofts where endless North Loop amenities are right out the front door. This historic building features one of the largest rooftop decks in the city with skyline views and fire pits to enjoy anytime. Head up to the fifth floor and enter to unit #503. Exposed brick, cement accents, 13 ft ceilings, and bright windows make this one bedroom condo shine. The open floor plan leads you into the heart of the home - the kitchen and living room. Here, curl up with a good book and a cup of hot cocoa this winter. The southwest facing windows let in the afternoon sunshine while taking in the Washington Avenue views. Refills are just steps away in the kitchen, which is complete with a newer refrigerator and center island. Enjoy in-unit laundry with the full bathroom, added storage in the bedroom with a full wall of closets, plus bonus loft. Never have to scrap your windshield thanks to a parking space in the heated garage, also with private storage! 2020-02-19

description: Recently sold: $900,000. The city is at your fingertips from this 1900's built loft in North Loop.Panoramic city views span the entire level of this 5th floor architecturalmasterpiece. Sliding glass doors separateexquisite living space and the 2 bedrooms located on opposite ends of theunit. Large storage area. 2 underground parking spaces.Pet friendly. When the sun sets the city comes to life, never miss anothermoment of it.

Morning coffee has never been better, sitting on your private patio, watching the sunrise over downtown Minneapolis. This condo is one of few two bedroom master suites, which each include large walk-in closets and full bathrooms. Master bedroom closet has been upgraded with ???California Closets Systems??? to give it a special touch. Walk to noteworthy award-winning restaurants, Target Field, Whole Foods, local shops, West River Parkway and the Greenway Trails. This is the luxury condo you've been waiting for!

description: Recently sold: $267,879.

Recently sold: $364,900. Location, location, location - Security Lofts Warehouse! Enjoy the city in the exact way you desire - in peace and quiet from your condo or walk to a Twins or Vikings game, farmers market, or a night out in the always happening North Loop. Also a very short walk away from the paths along the river. This condo has everything you need - in unit washer and dryer, convenient, heated, underground parking, a gym, community room, storage unit, & indoor bike storage. Plus you have access to all of the amenities at the 5th Ave Lofts - community room, rooftop deck, and gym. This condo is one of just a few in the city that provides a true loft experience - exposed wood beams, concrete flooring, wall of arch brick windows, granite counter tops, and stainless steel appliances - the condo is handsome and very low maintenance. Strong HOA, quiet neighbors, and pets are allowed. Association fee covers everything: outside maintenance, snow and lawn care, building maintenance, hazard insurance, security system, professional management, cable/internet, water/sewer, garbage, heating/air conditioning, and a PARKING SPACE. description:
Recently sold: $430,000. Available June 1. North Loop condo 1 block from river, Quiet boutique bldg. (55 units). Pets allowed. Wood floors, stainless steel appliances; 1 and 1/2 baths total, master bedroom has adjoining master bath; den or second bedroom with French doors, small 3rd room for use as study or guest room,  Juliet balcony looks out over 1st street north with skyline view. TWO heated parking spaces. 
Twins baseball 4 blocks, self-service bike rental 2 blocks. Biker? Runner? Walker? City bike path along the Mississippi River is right behind the building, Whole Foods 2 blocks, restaurants and coffee shop right downstairs. Work-out room in building, first floor.  Rooftop deck with outdoor grill and skyline views on 5th floor.  Standard pre-move-in Background/financial check is required by 212 Lofts Association.   Building has Comcast special low rates.

Building has HD  X-1 cable discount from Comcast for all residents, so cable is best deal available.

description:
For rent: $1,975. Live in a classic River Towers condominium! This condo is spacious, has lots of closets, wood floors in common areas, and large area for a dining table and chairs. There are cable outlets in LR and both BRs. The large windows face southwest for great sunlight and beautiful views of the Minneapolis skyline. And the windows open wide for great breezes. This is an extraordinarily well-built and well-maintained building with friendly and helpful staff, package service, recycling center, and indoor car wash. Great location (Hennepin) for quick access to many buses and light rail. Walk to three grocery stores and endless restaurants and bars, enjoy the Mississippi River one block away, cross it to visit the St. Anthony Main neighborhood. Grill, swim, or hang out in the largest and most beautiful courtyard (the whole block) in downtown Minneapolis.

Tenant pays for electricity ($35-$40) and optional internet (free wifi is available in the building's public spaces). Owner pays for all other utilities including basic cable TV. Deposit amount includes a non-refundable $150 tenant move-in fee, which is required by the condo association. Parking is separately contracted with the condo association and costs $55 for off street and $90 for underground garage.
